## Problem

Multiple students typing simultaneously → potential race conditions when directly writing to database.

Current WebSocket architecture: In-memory SessionManager serializes writes
Future Realtime architecture: Direct DB writes could conflict

## Solution: Optimistic Concurrency Control

Add version column to session_students table to detect concurrent modifications.

## Files to Create/Modify

**1. New Migration: supabase/migrations/YYYYMMDD_add_version_control.sql**
```sql
-- Add version column for optimistic locking
ALTER TABLE session_students 
ADD COLUMN version INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1;

-- Update API: increment version on each update
-- Client must provide current version, update fails if version mismatch
```

**2. Update API Route: src/app/api/sessions/[id]/code/route.ts**
```typescript
// Accept version in request body
interface CodeUpdateRequest {
  studentId: string;
  code: string;
  version: number; // Current version client has
}

// Update with version check
const result = await supabase
  .from('session_students')
  .update({ 
    code, 
    version: version + 1, 
    last_update: new Date() 
  })
  .eq('session_id', sessionId)
  .eq('student_id', studentId)
  .eq('version', version) // Only update if version matches
  .select();

if (result.data.length === 0) {
  // Version conflict - client has stale data
  return NextResponse.json({ 
    error: 'Version conflict - please reload' 
  }, { status: 409 });
}
```

**3. Update Hook: src/hooks/useRealtimeSession.ts**
```typescript
// Track version for each student
const [versions, setVersions] = useState<Map<string, number>>(new Map());

// Update version on Realtime message
useEffect(() => {
  if (lastMessage?.type === 'student_update') {
    const { student_id, version } = lastMessage.payload;
    setVersions(prev => new Map(prev).set(student_id, version));
  }
}, [lastMessage]);

// Include version in update request
const updateCode = async (studentId: string, code: string) => {
  const currentVersion = versions.get(studentId) || 1;
  const res = await fetch(`/api/sessions/${sessionId}/code`, {
    method: 'POST',
    body: JSON.stringify({ studentId, code, version: currentVersion }),
  });

  if (res.status === 409) {
    // Handle conflict - reload or merge
    console.warn('Version conflict detected');
  }
};
```

